app: Use Google Calendar to Publish Links to Facebook Page and Set to Repeat
description:
Use Google Calendar to Publish Links to Facebook Page and Set to Repeat Directions: You need to use one Google Calendar for each Facebook page you own. It also has to be from your main calendar, not additional calendar within your main calendar. 
(Step 1) - Create a new event in Google Calendar with the title #fblink 
(Step 2) - Edit the event and paste the link URL in the "Where" field in that calendar event.
(Step 3) -  Type your status message in the event's "Description" field and hit save.
(Step 4) - Schedule your "event" to repeat as often as desired. 

The trigger will fire within 15 minutes of the starting time of an "event" on your Google Calendar that contains the #fblink.  It will then create a new link post on your Facebook Page wall.  

That's it!

sentences.s: Use Google Calendar to Publish Links to Facebook Page and Set to Repeat Directions: You need to use one Google Calendar for each Facebook page you own.
It also has to be from your main calendar, not additional calendar within your main calendar.
(Step 1) - Create a new event in Google Calendar with the title #fblink
(Step 2) - Edit the event and paste the link URL in the "Where" field in that calendar event.
(Step 3) -  Type your status message in the event's "Description" field and hit save.
(Step 4) - Schedule your "event" to repeat as often as desired.
The trigger will fire within 15 minutes of the starting time of an "event" on your Google Calendar that contains the #fblink.
It will then create a new link post on your Facebook Page wall.
That's it!
